unittitle_ssm: Doris Ulmann Photograph Collection
abstract_ssm: The collection consists of ca. 3000 photographic prints, primarily platinum but some photogravure. Typical portrait subjects include prominent artists, authors, the Columbia University medical faculty, Johns Hopkins University medical faculty, and American editors. There are also examples of some of her best-known African-American and Appalachian photographs. Although many of the images are unidentified, they are the largest known body of prints made by Ulmann herself
corpname_ssm: Johns Hopkins University. School of Medicine -- Faculty -- Portraits
Columbia University. College of Physicians and Surgeons. Faculty -- Portraits
heading_ssm: Doris Ulmann Photograph Collection
